\n\"they would realise-if they never\nknew it before-that there is among\nCivil Service employ.. uinselfish and\nwholehearted devotion to the inter\nests of the United States; people who.\nnot in the exception but as a rule,\nthink first of the work and last of\nthemselves. if, indeed, at all.\n\"Feeling a I do, I want to assure\nyou all that my interest will not\ncease by reason of my leaving.\"\nAdmiral McGowan declared that he\nwas going to take a long vacation.\nGLAD TO RETIRE.\n\"I have no idea what I shell do or\nwhere I shall go,\" he said. But I do\nknow that, with the prospect of re\nmaining fourteen more years on the\nactive list of the Navy. I should have\nblocked the promotion of many of the\nbest men that ever wore the uniform\nof this country. fly retirIng and re\nsigning, I opened the way for the ap\npointment of another Itear Admiral\nin the Supply Corps and also created\na vacancy as Paymaster General with\nthe rank of Rear Admiral for a period\nof four years.\n\"To do this was my plain duty. I\nhave no regrets. I am glad I did It.''\nChiropractors to Meet.\nThe Maryland Chiropractors' Asso,\nclation, comtposed of licensed chiro\npractors of the State of Maryland and\nthe District of Columbia, will bold its\nquarterly meeting and lunchoon at the\n'ongroes Hail Hotel Sunday aftee\nD F\nM ExHANGE\ny W. HNAe Co.\nlioh. Jow A.M.\nMaahat. hirt... 8jij 31 IM\nMaati 11gat... 66 (A M\nMarl* eoen..... 33= 30% 10%\nMarine ad....... 4 48%j 48id\nMay Dept. Itore.. -8%M 4\nMezicas PoteS.. 1N 154 355\nMiua COI. Cs. lb 1514 359\nMidvals Steel-.. 13% 304 304\nMiddle tats... 124 12 12!6\nMina. 4 8L P. ILR 10) 10)j 10',\nMI.SL L P. MIa 7014 70 70'4\nMontgomer- -V. I9% 39 3 9%\nMo.. ILA Teos.- 24 216\nM.M&T.Ppfd.... 4% 4% 4%\nMe. PoG..... o- 0 19% M2\nMo. Pa1, ot..... 40% 40% 404\nNat.C.C........ 216 24 216\nNat. R. L M01. 4X 4A 44\nN.Y.Alr Brake.. 7 77 '8\nNov. CeO. Cop.. 9 E 3 Wj\nN. Y. O. a W... 18% 18% 381%\nN. Y. N. k. a. 154 8o 18)\nN. Y. Central...- 74 739i 73%